= Cardiology

== ECG & Arrhythmias

=== Complete Heart Block (CHB)
*ECG Findings:*
- P waves and QRS complexes have no relationship (AV dissociation)
- Atrial rate > Ventricular rate
- Ventricular rhythm regular, slow (30–40/min)

*Block kothay?*
- Usually at AV node or below (His–Purkinje system)

*Heart Rate:*
- Ventricular rate count korte hobe (300 ÷ big squares)

*Causes:*
- Degenerative fibrosis (Lenègre disease)
- Inferior MI
- Drugs (β‑blockers, digoxin)
- Congenital, myocarditis

*Treatment:*
- Acute: Atropine / Isoprenaline
- Definitive: Permanent pacemaker

*Conducting Pathway:*
- SA node → AV node → Bundle of His → Right & Left bundle branches → Purkinje fibers

*Other Blocks:*
- First degree, Second degree (Mobitz I, II)
- RBBB: rSR′ in V1
- LBBB: Broad notched R in V6

=== Supraventricular Tachycardia (SVT)
*ECG Findings:*
- Narrow QRS tachycardia
- HR 150–250/min
- P wave absent or hidden

*Types:*
- AVNRT, AVRT, Atrial tachycardia, AF, Atrial flutter

*Bedside Tests:*
- Carotid sinus massage
- Valsalva maneuver (forced expiration against closed glottis)

*Clinical Features:*
- Palpitation, dizziness, syncope

*Treatment:*
- Vagal maneuvers
- Adenosine (drug of choice)
- β‑blocker / Verapamil

*Non‑pharmacological:*
- Avoid caffeine, stress

=== Atrial Fibrillation (AF)
*ECG Findings:*
- Irregularly irregular rhythm
- Absent P waves
- Fibrillatory baseline

*Pulse:*
- Irregular, pulse deficit present

*Causes:*
- HTN, Mitral stenosis
- IHD, Thyrotoxicosis

*Complications:*
- Thromboembolism → Stroke

*Stroke Prophylaxis:*
- Anticoagulation (Warfarin, DOACs)

*Treatment:*
- Rate control: β‑blocker, Digoxin, CCB
- Rhythm control: Amiodarone

*Warfarin Toxicity:*
- Vitamin K, Fresh frozen plasma

=== Other Arrhythmias
- Sinus bradycardia: Athletes, hypothyroid, drugs
- Ventricular fibrillation: Most fatal arrhythmia → Defibrillation

== Ischemic Heart Disease

=== STEMI
*ECG:*
- ST elevation (transmural injury)
- Reciprocal ST depression

*Time Classification:*
- Hyperacute, Acute, Evolving, Old MI

*Treatment (MONA‑B):*
- Morphine, Oxygen, Nitrates, Aspirin
- β‑blocker, Reperfusion (PCI/Thrombolysis)

*Morphine Caution:*
- Respiratory depression → monitor RR

*Complications:*
- Acute: Arrhythmia, LVF, cardiogenic shock
- Chronic: Aneurysm, heart failure

*Inferior MI:*
- More arrhythmia (AV block)

*Risk Factors:*
- Smoking, DM, HTN, Dyslipidemia

