= Gastroenterology & Hepatology

== Diarrhea
*Acute Causes:*
- Infective (cholera, E. coli)
- Non‑infective (drug, food)

*Fluid Requirement:*
- 30–40 ml/kg/day + losses

*Chronic Diarrhea:*
- >4 weeks
- IBS, IBD, malabsorption

*Crohn vs UC:*
- Crohn: Skip lesions, transmural
- UC: Continuous, mucosal

== Acute Abdomen
*Causes:*
- Perforation, obstruction, pancreatitis

*PUD Perforation vs Obstruction:*
- Perforation: Sudden severe pain, rigidity
- Obstruction: Distension, vomiting

== GI Bleeding
- Hematemesis: Upper GI bleed
- Melena: Black tarry stool (upper GI)
- Hematochezia: Fresh blood (lower GI)

*PUD Cause:*
- NSAID, H. pylori

== Pancreas & Liver
*Acute Pancreatitis:*
- Epigastric pain radiating to back
- ↑ Amylase/Lipase
- Treatment: NPO, IV fluids, analgesia

*Chronic Pancreatitis:*
- Steatorrhea, diabetes

*CLD Stigmata:*
- Spider nevi, palmar erythema

*Hepatic Encephalopathy:*
- Asterixis, confusion
- Tx: Lactulose, Rifaximin

*HCC Hormones:*
- AFP, Erythropoietin

= Psychiatry

== Schizophrenia
- Duration ≥6 months
- Delusion, hallucination (auditory common)
- Drug: Flupentixol (depot IM)

== Mood Disorders
*Depression:*
- Low mood, anhedonia, sleep change
- Complication: Suicide
- Tx: SSRI, psychotherapy

*Bipolar:*
- Mania + Depression

*Mania Features:*
- Grandiosity, over‑talkative, flashy dress

== Others
- Somatoform: Physical symptoms without organic cause
- GAD: Excessive worry >6 months
- Alcohol effects: Liver, CNS, pancreas
- Eating disorders: Anorexia, Bulimia
- Post‑partum psychosis: Acute psychosis after delivery

= Rheumatology

== Rheumatoid Arthritis
*Findings:*
- Ulnar deviation, swan neck deformity

*Criteria:*
- Symmetrical polyarthritis, RF positive

*Drugs:*
- DMARDs: Methotrexate, Sulfasalazine

*Methotrexate:*
- Dose: 7.5–25 mg/week
- Complication: Pancytopenia
- Tx: Folic acid

== Arthralgia
- Viral arthralgia post‑fever
- Common cause: Chikungunya
- Lice fever: Typhus

